48 void llvm::initializeCore(PassRegistry &Registry) {
49  initializeDominatorTreeWrapperPassPass(Registry);
50  initializePrintModulePassWrapperPass(Registry);
51  initializePrintFunctionPassWrapperPass(Registry);
52  initializeSafepointIRVerifierPass(Registry);
53  initializeVerifierLegacyPassPass(Registry);
54 }

57  initializeCore(*unwrap(R));
58 }

66 void LLVMGetVersion(unsigned *Major, unsigned *Minor, unsigned *Patch) {
67  if (Major)
68  *Major = LLVM_VERSION_MAJOR;
69  if (Minor)
70  *Minor = LLVM_VERSION_MINOR;
71  if (Patch)
72  *Patch = LLVM_VERSION_PATCH;
73 }

153 LLVMAttributeRef LLVMCreateEnumAttribute(LLVMContextRef C, unsigned KindID,
154  uint64_t Val) {
155  auto &Ctx = *unwrap(C);
156  auto AttrKind = (Attribute::AttrKind)KindID;
157  return wrap(Attribute::get(Ctx, AttrKind, Val));
158 }

164 uint64_t LLVMGetEnumAttributeValue(LLVMAttributeRef A) {
165  auto Attr = unwrap(A);
166  if (Attr.isEnumAttribute())
167  return 0;
168  return Attr.getValueAsInt();
169 }

173  auto &Ctx = *unwrap(C);
174  auto AttrKind = (Attribute::AttrKind)KindID;
175  return wrap(Attribute::get(Ctx, AttrKind, unwrap(type_ref)));
176 }

217 char *LLVMGetDiagInfoDescription(LLVMDiagnosticInfoRef DI) {
218  std::string MsgStorage;
219  raw_string_ostream Stream(MsgStorage);
220  DiagnosticPrinterRawOStream DP(Stream);
221 
222  unwrap(DI)->print(DP);
223  Stream.flush();
224 
225  return LLVMCreateMessage(MsgStorage.c_str());
226 }
227 
228 LLVMDiagnosticSeverity LLVMGetDiagInfoSeverity(LLVMDiagnosticInfoRef DI) {
229  LLVMDiagnosticSeverity severity;
230 
231  switch(unwrap(DI)->getSeverity()) {
232  default:
233  severity = LLVMDSError;
234  break;
235  case DS_Warning:
236  severity = LLVMDSWarning;
237  break;
238  case DS_Remark:
239  severity = LLVMDSRemark;
240  break;
241  case DS_Note:
242  severity = LLVMDSNote;
243  break;
244  }
245 
246  return severity;
247 }

306 /*--.. Module flags ........................................................--*/
307 struct LLVMOpaqueModuleFlagEntry {
308  LLVMModuleFlagBehavior Behavior;
309  const char *Key;
310  size_t KeyLen;
311  LLVMMetadataRef Metadata;
312 };
313 
314 static Module::ModFlagBehavior
315 map_to_llvmModFlagBehavior(LLVMModuleFlagBehavior Behavior) {
316  switch (Behavior) {
317  case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorError:
318  return Module::ModFlagBehavior::Error;
319  case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorWarning:
320  return Module::ModFlagBehavior::Warning;
321  case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorRequire:
322  return Module::ModFlagBehavior::Require;
323  case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorOverride:
324  return Module::ModFlagBehavior::Override;
325  case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorAppend:
326  return Module::ModFlagBehavior::Append;
327  case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorAppendUnique:
328  return Module::ModFlagBehavior::AppendUnique;
329  }
330  llvm_unreachable("Unknown LLVMModuleFlagBehavior");
331 }
332 
333 static LLVMModuleFlagBehavior
334 map_from_llvmModFlagBehavior(Module::ModFlagBehavior Behavior) {
335  switch (Behavior) {
336  case Module::ModFlagBehavior::Error:
337  return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorError;
338  case Module::ModFlagBehavior::Warning:
339  return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorWarning;
340  case Module::ModFlagBehavior::Require:
341  return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorRequire;
342  case Module::ModFlagBehavior::Override:
343  return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorOverride;
344  case Module::ModFlagBehavior::Append:
345  return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorAppend;
346  case Module::ModFlagBehavior::AppendUnique:
347  return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorAppendUnique;
348  default:
349  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled Flag Behavior");
350  }
351 }
352 
353 LLVMModuleFlagEntry *LLVMCopyModuleFlagsMetadata(LLVMModuleRef M, size_t *Len) {
354  SmallVector<Module::ModuleFlagEntry, 8> MFEs;
355  unwrap(M)->getModuleFlagsMetadata(MFEs);
356 
357  LLVMOpaqueModuleFlagEntry *Result = static_cast<LLVMOpaqueModuleFlagEntry *>(
358  safe_malloc(MFEs.size() * sizeof(LLVMOpaqueModuleFlagEntry)));
359  for (unsigned i = 0; i < MFEs.size(); ++i) {
360  const auto &ModuleFlag = MFEs[i];
361  Result[i].Behavior = map_from_llvmModFlagBehavior(ModuleFlag.Behavior);
362  Result[i].Key = ModuleFlag.Key->getString().data();
363  Result[i].KeyLen = ModuleFlag.Key->getString().size();
364  Result[i].Metadata = wrap(ModuleFlag.Val);
365  }
366  *Len = MFEs.size();
367  return Result;
368 }
369 
370 void LLVMDisposeModuleFlagsMetadata(LLVMModuleFlagEntry *Entries) {
371  free(Entries);
372 }
373 
374 LLVMModuleFlagBehavior
375 LLVMModuleFlagEntriesGetFlagBehavior(LLVMModuleFlagEntry *Entries,
376  unsigned Index) {
377  LLVMOpaqueModuleFlagEntry MFE =
378  static_cast<LLVMOpaqueModuleFlagEntry>(Entries[Index]);
379  return MFE.Behavior;
380 }
381 
382 const char *LLVMModuleFlagEntriesGetKey(LLVMModuleFlagEntry *Entries,
383  unsigned Index, size_t *Len) {
384  LLVMOpaqueModuleFlagEntry MFE =
385  static_cast<LLVMOpaqueModuleFlagEntry>(Entries[Index]);
386  *Len = MFE.KeyLen;
387  return MFE.Key;
388 }

402 void LLVMAddModuleFlag(LLVMModuleRef M, LLVMModuleFlagBehavior Behavior,
403  const char *Key, size_t KeyLen,
404  LLVMMetadataRef Val) {

411 void LLVMDumpModule(LLVMModuleRef M) {
412  unwrap(M)->print(errs(), nullptr,
413  /*ShouldPreserveUseListOrder=*/false, /*IsForDebug=*/true);
414 }
415 
416 LLVMBool LLVMPrintModuleToFile(LLVMModuleRef M, const char *Filename,
417  char **ErrorMessage) {
418  std::error_code EC;
419  raw_fd_ostream dest(Filename, EC, sys::fs::OF_TextWithCRLF);
420  if (EC) {
421  *ErrorMessage = strdup(EC.message().c_str());
422  return true;
423  }
424 
425  unwrap(M)->print(dest, nullptr);
426 
427  dest.close();
428 
429  if (dest.has_error()) {
430  std::string E = "Error printing to file: " + dest.error().message();
431  *ErrorMessage = strdup(E.c_str());
432  return true;
433  }
434 
435  return false;
436 }

467 LLVMValueRef LLVMGetInlineAsm(LLVMTypeRef Ty, char *AsmString,
468  size_t AsmStringSize, char *Constraints,
469  size_t ConstraintsSize, LLVMBool HasSideEffects,
470  LLVMBool IsAlignStack,
471  LLVMInlineAsmDialect Dialect, LLVMBool CanThrow) {
472  InlineAsm::AsmDialect AD;
473  switch (Dialect) {
474  case LLVMInlineAsmDialectATT:
475  AD = InlineAsm::AD_ATT;
476  break;
477  case LLVMInlineAsmDialectIntel:
478  AD = InlineAsm::AD_Intel;
479  break;
480  }
481  return wrap(InlineAsm::get(unwrap<FunctionType>(Ty),
482  StringRef(AsmString, AsmStringSize),
483  StringRef(Constraints, ConstraintsSize),
484  HasSideEffects, IsAlignStack, AD, CanThrow));
485 }

495 /*--.. Operations on all types (mostly) ....................................--*/

497 LLVMTypeKind LLVMGetTypeKind(LLVMTypeRef Ty) {
498  switch (unwrap(Ty)->getTypeID()) {
499  case Type::VoidTyID:
500  return LLVMVoidTypeKind;
501  case Type::HalfTyID:
502  return LLVMHalfTypeKind;
503  case Type::BFloatTyID:
504  return LLVMBFloatTypeKind;
505  case Type::FloatTyID:
506  return LLVMFloatTypeKind;
507  case Type::DoubleTyID:
508  return LLVMDoubleTypeKind;
509  case Type::X86_FP80TyID:
510  return LLVMX86_FP80TypeKind;
511  case Type::FP128TyID:
512  return LLVMFP128TypeKind;
513  case Type::PPC_FP128TyID:
514  return LLVMPPC_FP128TypeKind;
515  case Type::LabelTyID:
516  return LLVMLabelTypeKind;
517  case Type::MetadataTyID:
518  return LLVMMetadataTypeKind;
519  case Type::IntegerTyID:
520  return LLVMIntegerTypeKind;
521  case Type::FunctionTyID:
522  return LLVMFunctionTypeKind;
523  case Type::StructTyID:
524  return LLVMStructTypeKind;
525  case Type::ArrayTyID:
526  return LLVMArrayTypeKind;
527  case Type::PointerTyID:
528  return LLVMPointerTypeKind;
529  case Type::FixedVectorTyID:
530  return LLVMVectorTypeKind;
531  case Type::X86_MMXTyID:
532  return LLVMX86_MMXTypeKind;
533  case Type::X86_AMXTyID:
534  return LLVMX86_AMXTypeKind;
535  case Type::TokenTyID:
536  return LLVMTokenTypeKind;
537  case Type::ScalableVectorTyID:
538  return LLVMScalableVectorTypeKind;
539  case Type::TargetExtTyID:
540  return LLVMTargetExtTypeKind;
541  case Type::TypedPointerTyID:
542  llvm_unreachable("Typed pointers are unsupported via the C API");
543  }
544  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled TypeID.");
545 }

560 char *LLVMPrintTypeToString(LLVMTypeRef Ty) {
561  std::string buf;
562  raw_string_ostream os(buf);
563 
564  if (unwrap(Ty))
565  unwrap(Ty)->print(os);
566  else
567  os << "Printing <null> Type";
568 
569  os.flush();
570 
571  return strdup(buf.c_str());
572 }

886 LLVMValueKind LLVMGetValueKind(LLVMValueRef Val) {
887  switch(unwrap(Val)->getValueID()) {
888 #define LLVM_C_API 1
889 #define HANDLE_VALUE(Name) \
890  case Value::Name##Val: \
891  return LLVM##Name##ValueKind;
892 #include "llvm/IR/Value.def"
893  default:
894  return LLVMInstructionValueKind;
895  }

942 LLVMValueRef LLVMGetMetadata(LLVMValueRef Inst, unsigned KindID) {
943  auto *I = unwrap<Instruction>(Inst);
944  assert(I && "Expected instruction");
945  if (auto *MD = I->getMetadata(KindID))
946  return wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(I->getContext(), MD));
947  return nullptr;
948 }
949 
950 // MetadataAsValue uses a canonical format which strips the actual MDNode for
951 // MDNode with just a single constant value, storing just a ConstantAsMetadata
952 // This undoes this canonicalization, reconstructing the MDNode.
953 static MDNode *extractMDNode(MetadataAsValue *MAV) {
954  Metadata *MD = MAV->getMetadata();
955  assert((isa<MDNode>(MD) || isa<ConstantAsMetadata>(MD)) &&
956  "Expected a metadata node or a canonicalized constant");
957 
958  if (MDNode *N = dyn_cast<MDNode>(MD))
959  return N;
960 
961  return MDNode::get(MAV->getContext(), MD);
962 }
963 
964 void LLVMSetMetadata(LLVMValueRef Inst, unsigned KindID, LLVMValueRef Val) {
965  MDNode *N = Val ? extractMDNode(unwrap<MetadataAsValue>(Val)) : nullptr;
966 
967  unwrap<Instruction>(Inst)->setMetadata(KindID, N);
968 }
969 
970 struct LLVMOpaqueValueMetadataEntry {
971  unsigned Kind;
972  LLVMMetadataRef Metadata;
973 };
974 
975 using MetadataEntries = SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>>;
976 static LLVMValueMetadataEntry *
977 llvm_getMetadata(size_t *NumEntries,
978  llvm::function_ref<void(MetadataEntries &)> AccessMD) {
979  SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>, 8> MVEs;
980  AccessMD(MVEs);
981 
982  LLVMOpaqueValueMetadataEntry *Result =
983  static_cast<LLVMOpaqueValueMetadataEntry *>(
984  safe_malloc(MVEs.size() * sizeof(LLVMOpaqueValueMetadataEntry)));
985  for (unsigned i = 0; i < MVEs.size(); ++i) {
986  const auto &ModuleFlag = MVEs[i];
987  Result[i].Kind = ModuleFlag.first;
988  Result[i].Metadata = wrap(ModuleFlag.second);
989  }
990  *NumEntries = MVEs.size();
991  return Result;
992 }
993 
994 LLVMValueMetadataEntry *
995 LLVMInstructionGetAllMetadataOtherThanDebugLoc(LLVMValueRef Value,
996  size_t *NumEntries) {
997  return llvm_getMetadata(NumEntries, [&Value](MetadataEntries &Entries) {
998  Entries.clear();
999  unwrap<Instruction>(Value)->getAllMetadata(Entries);
1000  });
1001 }

1060 static LLVMValueRef getMDNodeOperandImpl(LLVMContext &Context, const MDNode *N,
1061  unsigned Index) {
1062  Metadata *Op = N->getOperand(Index);
1063  if (!Op)
1064  return nullptr;
1065  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantAsMetadata>(Op))
1066  return wrap(C->getValue());
1067  return wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(Context, Op));
1068 }
1069 
1070 LLVMValueRef LLVMGetOperand(LLVMValueRef Val, unsigned Index) {
1071  Value *V = unwrap(Val);
1072  if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<MetadataAsValue>(V)) {
1073  if (auto *L = dyn_cast<ValueAsMetadata>(MD->getMetadata())) {
1074  assert(Index == 0 && "Function-local metadata can only have one operand");
1075  return wrap(L->getValue());
1076  }
1077  return getMDNodeOperandImpl(V->getContext(),
1078  cast<MDNode>(MD->getMetadata()), Index);
1079  }
1080 
1081  return wrap(cast<User>(V)->getOperand(Index));
1082 }
1083

1085  Value *V = unwrap(Val);
1086  return wrap(&cast<User>(V)->getOperandUse(Index));
1087 }

1163 
1164 LLVMValueRef LLVMMDNodeInContext(LLVMContextRef C, LLVMValueRef *Vals,
1165  unsigned Count) {
1166  LLVMContext &Context = *unwrap(C);
1167  SmallVector<Metadata *, 8> MDs;
1168  for (auto *OV : ArrayRef(Vals, Count)) {
1169  Value *V = unwrap(OV);
1170  Metadata *MD;
1171  if (!V)
1172  MD = nullptr;
1173  else if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V))
1174  MD = ConstantAsMetadata::get(C);
1175  else if (auto *MDV = dyn_cast<MetadataAsValue>(V)) {
1176  MD = MDV->getMetadata();
1177  assert(!isa<LocalAsMetadata>(MD) && "Unexpected function-local metadata "
1178  "outside of direct argument to call");
1179  } else {
1180  // This is function-local metadata. Pretend to make an MDNode.
1181  assert(Count == 1 &&
1182  "Expected only one operand to function-local metadata");
1183  return wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(Context, LocalAsMetadata::get(V)));
1184  }
1185 
1186  MDs.push_back(MD);
1187  }
1188  return wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(Context, MDNode::get(Context, MDs)));
1189 }

1192  return LLVMMDNodeInContext(LLVMGetGlobalContext(), Vals, Count);
1193 }

1200  auto *V = unwrap(Val);
1201  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V))
1202  return wrap(ConstantAsMetadata::get(C));
1203  if (auto *MAV = dyn_cast<MetadataAsValue>(V))
1204  return wrap(MAV->getMetadata());
1205  return wrap(ValueAsMetadata::get(V));
1206 }

1208 const char *LLVMGetMDString(LLVMValueRef V, unsigned *Length) {

1210  if (const MDString *S = dyn_cast<MDString>(MD->getMetadata())) {
1211  *Length = S->getString().size();
1212  return S->getString().data();
1213  }
1214  *Length = 0;
1215  return nullptr;
1216 }

1267 const char *LLVMGetNamedMetadataName(LLVMNamedMDNodeRef NMD, size_t *NameLen) {
1268  NamedMDNode *NamedNode = unwrap(NMD);
1269  *NameLen = NamedNode->getName().size();
1270  return NamedNode->getName().data();
1271 }
1272 
1273 void LLVMGetMDNodeOperands(LLVMValueRef V, LLVMValueRef *Dest) {
1274  auto *MD = unwrap<MetadataAsValue>(V);
1275  if (auto *MDV = dyn_cast<ValueAsMetadata>(MD->getMetadata())) {
1276  *Dest = wrap(MDV->getValue());
1277  return;
1278  }
1279  const auto *N = cast<MDNode>(MD->getMetadata());
1280  const unsigned numOperands = N->getNumOperands();
1281  LLVMContext &Context = unwrap(V)->getContext();
1282  for (unsigned i = 0; i < numOperands; i++)
1283  Dest[i] = getMDNodeOperandImpl(Context, N, i);
1284 }
1285 
1286 void LLVMReplaceMDNodeOperandWith(LLVMValueRef V, unsigned Index,
1287  LLVMMetadataRef Replacement) {
1288  auto *MD = cast<MetadataAsValue>(unwrap(V));
1289  auto *N = cast<MDNode>(MD->getMetadata());
1290  N->replaceOperandWith(Index, unwrap<Metadata>(Replacement));
1291 }
1292 
1293 unsigned LLVMGetNamedMetadataNumOperands(LLVMModuleRef M, const char *Name) {
1294  if (NamedMDNode *N = unwrap(M)->getNamedMetadata(Name)) {
1295  return N->getNumOperands();
1296  }
1297  return 0;
1298 }
1299 
1300 void LLVMGetNamedMetadataOperands(LLVMModuleRef M, const char *Name,
1301  LLVMValueRef *Dest) {
1302  NamedMDNode *N = unwrap(M)->getNamedMetadata(Name);
1303  if (!N)
1304  return;
1305  LLVMContext &Context = unwrap(M)->getContext();
1306  for (unsigned i=0;i<N->getNumOperands();i++)
1307  Dest[i] = wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(Context, N->getOperand(i)));
1308 }
1309 
1310 void LLVMAddNamedMetadataOperand(LLVMModuleRef M, const char *Name,
1311  LLVMValueRef Val) {
1312  NamedMDNode *N = unwrap(M)->getOrInsertNamedMetadata(Name);
1313  if (!N)
1314  return;
1315  if (!Val)
1316  return;
1317  N->addOperand(extractMDNode(unwrap<MetadataAsValue>(Val)));
1318 }
1319 
1320 const char *LLVMGetDebugLocDirectory(LLVMValueRef Val, unsigned *Length) {
1321  if (!Length) return nullptr;
1322  StringRef S;
1323  if (const auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(unwrap(Val))) {
1324  if (const auto &DL = I->getDebugLoc()) {
1325  S = DL->getDirectory();
1326  }
1327  } else if (const auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(unwrap(Val))) {
1328  SmallVector<DIGlobalVariableExpression *, 1> GVEs;
1329  GV->getDebugInfo(GVEs);
1330  if (GVEs.size())
1331  if (const DIGlobalVariable *DGV = GVEs[0]->getVariable())
1332  S = DGV->getDirectory();
1333  } else if (const auto *F = dyn_cast<Function>(unwrap(Val))) {
1334  if (const DISubprogram *DSP = F->getSubprogram())
1335  S = DSP->getDirectory();
1336  } else {
1337  assert(0 && "Expected Instruction, GlobalVariable or Function");
1338  return nullptr;
1339  }
1340  *Length = S.size();
1341  return S.data();
1342 }
1343 
1344 const char *LLVMGetDebugLocFilename(LLVMValueRef Val, unsigned *Length) {
1345  if (!Length) return nullptr;
1346  StringRef S;
1347  if (const auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(unwrap(Val))) {
1348  if (const auto &DL = I->getDebugLoc()) {
1349  S = DL->getFilename();
1350  }
1351  } else if (const auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(unwrap(Val))) {
1352  SmallVector<DIGlobalVariableExpression *, 1> GVEs;
1353  GV->getDebugInfo(GVEs);
1354  if (GVEs.size())
1355  if (const DIGlobalVariable *DGV = GVEs[0]->getVariable())
1356  S = DGV->getFilename();
1357  } else if (const auto *F = dyn_cast<Function>(unwrap(Val))) {
1358  if (const DISubprogram *DSP = F->getSubprogram())
1359  S = DSP->getFilename();
1360  } else {
1361  assert(0 && "Expected Instruction, GlobalVariable or Function");
1362  return nullptr;
1363  }
1364  *Length = S.size();
1365  return S.data();
1366 }
1367 
1368 unsigned LLVMGetDebugLocLine(LLVMValueRef Val) {
1369  unsigned L = 0;
1370  if (const auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(unwrap(Val))) {
1371  if (const auto &DL = I->getDebugLoc()) {
1372  L = DL->getLine();
1373  }
1374  } else if (const auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(unwrap(Val))) {
1375  SmallVector<DIGlobalVariableExpression *, 1> GVEs;
1376  GV->getDebugInfo(GVEs);
1377  if (GVEs.size())
1378  if (const DIGlobalVariable *DGV = GVEs[0]->getVariable())
1379  L = DGV->getLine();
1380  } else if (const auto *F = dyn_cast<Function>(unwrap(Val))) {
1381  if (const DISubprogram *DSP = F->getSubprogram())
1382  L = DSP->getLine();
1383  } else {
1384  assert(0 && "Expected Instruction, GlobalVariable or Function");
1385  return -1;
1386  }
1387  return L;
1388 }
1389 
1390 unsigned LLVMGetDebugLocColumn(LLVMValueRef Val) {
1391  unsigned C = 0;
1392  if (const auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(unwrap(Val)))
1393  if (const auto &DL = I->getDebugLoc())
1394  C = DL->getColumn();
1395  return C;
1396 }

1446 double LLVMConstRealGetDouble(LLVMValueRef ConstantVal, LLVMBool *LosesInfo) {
1447  ConstantFP *cFP = unwrap<ConstantFP>(ConstantVal) ;
1448  Type *Ty = cFP->getType();
1449 
1450  if (Ty->isHalfTy() || Ty->isBFloatTy() || Ty->isFloatTy() ||
1451  Ty->isDoubleTy()) {
1452  *LosesInfo = false;
1453  return cFP->getValueAPF().convertToDouble();
1454  }
1455 
1456  bool APFLosesInfo;
1457  APFloat APF = cFP->getValueAPF();
1458  APF.convert(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &APFLosesInfo);
1459  *LosesInfo = APFLosesInfo;
1460  return APF.convertToDouble();
1461 }

1471  DontNullTerminate == 0));

1538 /*-- Opcode mapping */
1539 
1540 static LLVMOpcode map_to_llvmopcode(int opcode)
1541 {
1542  switch (opcode) {
1543  default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled Opcode.");
1544 #define HANDLE_INST(num, opc, clas) case num: return LLVM##opc;
1545 #include "llvm/IR/Instruction.def"
1546 #undef HANDLE_INST
1547  }
1548 }
1549 
1550 static int map_from_llvmopcode(LLVMOpcode code)
1551 {
1552  switch (code) {
1553 #define HANDLE_INST(num, opc, clas) case LLVM##opc: return num;
1554 #include "llvm/IR/Instruction.def"
1555 #undef HANDLE_INST
1556  }
1557  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled Opcode.");
1558 }

1564 }

1832  unwrap<Constant>(VectorBConstant),
1833  IntMask));

1858 LLVMLinkage LLVMGetLinkage(LLVMValueRef Global) {
1859  switch (unwrap<GlobalValue>(Global)->getLinkage()) {
1860  case GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage:
1861  return LLVMExternalLinkage;
1862  case GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage:
1863  return LLVMAvailableExternallyLinkage;
1864  case GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage:
1865  return LLVMLinkOnceAnyLinkage;
1866  case GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage:
1867  return LLVMLinkOnceODRLinkage;
1868  case GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage:
1869  return LLVMWeakAnyLinkage;
1870  case GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage:
1871  return LLVMWeakODRLinkage;
1872  case GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage:
1873  return LLVMAppendingLinkage;
1874  case GlobalValue::InternalLinkage:
1875  return LLVMInternalLinkage;
1876  case GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage:
1877  return LLVMPrivateLinkage;
1878  case GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage:
1879  return LLVMExternalWeakLinkage;
1880  case GlobalValue::CommonLinkage:
1881  return LLVMCommonLinkage;
1882  }
1883 
1884  llvm_unreachable("Invalid GlobalValue linkage!");
1885 }
1886 
1887 void LLVMSetLinkage(LLVMValueRef Global, LLVMLinkage Linkage) {
1888  GlobalValue *GV = unwrap<GlobalValue>(Global);
1889 
1890  switch (Linkage) {
1891  case LLVMExternalLinkage:
1892  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
1893  break;
1894  case LLVMAvailableExternallyLinkage:
1895  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage);
1896  break;
1897  case LLVMLinkOnceAnyLinkage:
1898  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage);
1899  break;
1900  case LLVMLinkOnceODRLinkage:
1901  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage);
1902  break;
1903  case LLVMLinkOnceODRAutoHideLinkage:
1904  LLVM_DEBUG(
1905  errs() << "LLVMSetLinkage(): LLVMLinkOnceODRAutoHideLinkage is no "
1906  "longer supported.");
1907  break;
1908  case LLVMWeakAnyLinkage:
1909  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage);
1910  break;
1911  case LLVMWeakODRLinkage:
1912  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage);
1913  break;
1914  case LLVMAppendingLinkage:
1915  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage);
1916  break;
1917  case LLVMInternalLinkage:
1918  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::InternalLinkage);
1919  break;
1920  case LLVMPrivateLinkage:
1921  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage);
1922  break;
1923  case LLVMLinkerPrivateLinkage:
1924  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage);
1925  break;
1926  case LLVMLinkerPrivateWeakLinkage:
1927  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage);
1928  break;
1929  case LLVMDLLImportLinkage:
1930  LLVM_DEBUG(
1931  errs()
1932  << "LLVMSetLinkage(): LLVMDLLImportLinkage is no longer supported.");
1933  break;
1934  case LLVMDLLExportLinkage:
1935  LLVM_DEBUG(
1936  errs()
1937  << "LLVMSetLinkage(): LLVMDLLExportLinkage is no longer supported.");
1938  break;
1939  case LLVMExternalWeakLinkage:
1940  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage);
1941  break;
1942  case LLVMGhostLinkage:
1943  LLVM_DEBUG(
1944  errs() << "LLVMSetLinkage(): LLVMGhostLinkage is no longer supported.");
1945  break;
1946  case LLVMCommonLinkage:
1947  GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::CommonLinkage);
1948  break;
1949  }
1950 }

2021 /*--.. Operations on global variables, load and store instructions .........--*/
2022 
2023 unsigned LLVMGetAlignment(LLVMValueRef V) {
2024  Value *P = unwrap(V);
2025  if (GlobalObject *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalObject>(P))
2026  return GV->getAlign() ? GV->getAlign()->value() : 0;
2027  if (AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(P))
2028  return AI->getAlign().value();
2029  if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(P))
2030  return LI->getAlign().value();
2031  if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(P))
2032  return SI->getAlign().value();
2033  if (AtomicRMWInst *RMWI = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(P))
2034  return RMWI->getAlign().value();
2035  if (AtomicCmpXchgInst *CXI = dyn_cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(P))
2036  return CXI->getAlign().value();
2037 
2038  llvm_unreachable(
2039  "only GlobalValue, AllocaInst, LoadInst, StoreInst, AtomicRMWInst, "
2040  "and AtomicCmpXchgInst have alignment");
2041 }
2042 
2043 void LLVMSetAlignment(LLVMValueRef V, unsigned Bytes) {
2044  Value *P = unwrap(V);
2045  if (GlobalObject *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalObject>(P))
2046  GV->setAlignment(MaybeAlign(Bytes));
2047  else if (AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(P))
2048  AI->setAlignment(Align(Bytes));
2049  else if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(P))
2050  LI->setAlignment(Align(Bytes));
2051  else if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(P))
2052  SI->setAlignment(Align(Bytes));
2053  else if (AtomicRMWInst *RMWI = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(P))
2054  RMWI->setAlignment(Align(Bytes));
2055  else if (AtomicCmpXchgInst *CXI = dyn_cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(P))
2056  CXI->setAlignment(Align(Bytes));
2057  else
2058  llvm_unreachable(
2059  "only GlobalValue, AllocaInst, LoadInst, StoreInst, AtomicRMWInst, and "
2060  "and AtomicCmpXchgInst have alignment");
2061 }

2063 LLVMValueMetadataEntry *LLVMGlobalCopyAllMetadata(LLVMValueRef Value,
2064  size_t *NumEntries) {
2065  return llvm_getMetadata(NumEntries, [&Value](MetadataEntries &Entries) {
2066  Entries.clear();
2067  if (Instruction *Instr = dyn_cast<Instruction>(unwrap(Value))) {
2068  Instr->getAllMetadata(Entries);
2069  } else {
2070  unwrap<GlobalObject>(Value)->getAllMetadata(Entries);
2071  }
2072  });
2073 }

2997 void LLVMAddIncoming(LLVMValueRef PhiNode, LLVMValueRef *IncomingValues,
2998  LLVMBasicBlockRef *IncomingBlocks, unsigned Count) {
2999  PHINode *PhiVal = unwrap<PHINode>(PhiNode);
3000  for (unsigned I = 0; I != Count; ++I)
3001  PhiVal->addIncoming(unwrap(IncomingValues[I]), unwrap(IncomingBlocks[I]));

3016 /*--.. Operations on extractvalue and insertvalue nodes ....................--*/
3017 
3018 unsigned LLVMGetNumIndices(LLVMValueRef Inst) {
3019  auto *I = unwrap(Inst);
3020  if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(I))
3021  return GEP->getNumIndices();
3022  if (auto *EV = dyn_cast<ExtractValueInst>(I))
3023  return EV->getNumIndices();
3024  if (auto *IV = dyn_cast<InsertValueInst>(I))
3025  return IV->getNumIndices();
3026  llvm_unreachable(
3027  "LLVMGetNumIndices applies only to extractvalue and insertvalue!");
3028 }
3029 
3030 const unsigned *LLVMGetIndices(LLVMValueRef Inst) {
3031  auto *I = unwrap(Inst);
3032  if (auto *EV = dyn_cast<ExtractValueInst>(I))
3033  return EV->getIndices().data();
3034  if (auto *IV = dyn_cast<InsertValueInst>(I))
3035  return IV->getIndices().data();
3036  llvm_unreachable(
3037  "LLVMGetIndices applies only to extractvalue and insertvalue!");
3038 }

3177 LLVMValueRef LLVMBuildLandingPad(LLVMBuilderRef B, LLVMTypeRef Ty,
3178  LLVMValueRef PersFn, unsigned NumClauses,
3179  const char *Name) {
3180  // The personality used to live on the landingpad instruction, but now it
3181  // lives on the parent function. For compatibility, take the provided
3182  // personality and put it on the parent function.
3183  if (PersFn)
3184  unwrap(B)->GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->setPersonalityFn(
3185  unwrap<Function>(PersFn));
3186  return wrap(unwrap(B)->CreateLandingPad(unwrap(Ty), NumClauses, Name));
3187 }

3462 
3463 LLVMValueRef LLVMBuildMalloc(LLVMBuilderRef B, LLVMTypeRef Ty,
3464  const char *Name) {
3465  Type* ITy = Type::getInt32Ty(unwrap(B)->GetInsertBlock()->getContext());
3466  Constant* AllocSize = ConstantExpr::getSizeOf(unwrap(Ty));
3467  AllocSize = ConstantExpr::getTruncOrBitCast(AllocSize, ITy);
3468  Instruction* Malloc = CallInst::CreateMalloc(unwrap(B)->GetInsertBlock(),
3469  ITy, unwrap(Ty), AllocSize,
3470  nullptr, nullptr, "");
3471  return wrap(unwrap(B)->Insert(Malloc, Twine(Name)));
3472 }
3473 
3474 LLVMValueRef LLVMBuildArrayMalloc(LLVMBuilderRef B, LLVMTypeRef Ty,
3475  LLVMValueRef Val, const char *Name) {
3476  Type* ITy = Type::getInt32Ty(unwrap(B)->GetInsertBlock()->getContext());
3477  Constant* AllocSize = ConstantExpr::getSizeOf(unwrap(Ty));
3478  AllocSize = ConstantExpr::getTruncOrBitCast(AllocSize, ITy);
3479  Instruction* Malloc = CallInst::CreateMalloc(unwrap(B)->GetInsertBlock(),
3480  ITy, unwrap(Ty), AllocSize,
3481  unwrap(Val), nullptr, "");
3482  return wrap(unwrap(B)->Insert(Malloc, Twine(Name)));
3483 }

3535 static AtomicOrdering mapFromLLVMOrdering(LLVMAtomicOrdering Ordering) {
3536  switch (Ordering) {
3537  case LLVMAtomicOrderingNotAtomic: return AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic;
3538  case LLVMAtomicOrderingUnordered: return AtomicOrdering::Unordered;
3539  case LLVMAtomicOrderingMonotonic: return AtomicOrdering::Monotonic;
3540  case LLVMAtomicOrderingAcquire: return AtomicOrdering::Acquire;
3541  case LLVMAtomicOrderingRelease: return AtomicOrdering::Release;
3542  case LLVMAtomicOrderingAcquireRelease:
3543  return AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease;
3544  case LLVMAtomicOrderingSequentiallyConsistent:
3545  return AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent;
3546  }
3547 
3548  llvm_unreachable("Invalid LLVMAtomicOrdering value!");
3549 }
3550 
3551 static LLVMAtomicOrdering mapToLLVMOrdering(AtomicOrdering Ordering) {
3552  switch (Ordering) {
3553  case AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic: return LLVMAtomicOrderingNotAtomic;
3554  case AtomicOrdering::Unordered: return LLVMAtomicOrderingUnordered;
3555  case AtomicOrdering::Monotonic: return LLVMAtomicOrderingMonotonic;
3556  case AtomicOrdering::Acquire: return LLVMAtomicOrderingAcquire;
3557  case AtomicOrdering::Release: return LLVMAtomicOrderingRelease;
3558  case AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease:
3559  return LLVMAtomicOrderingAcquireRelease;
3560  case AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent:
3561  return LLVMAtomicOrderingSequentiallyConsistent;
3562  }
3563 
3564  llvm_unreachable("Invalid AtomicOrdering value!");
3565 }
3566 
3567 static AtomicRMWInst::BinOp mapFromLLVMRMWBinOp(LLVMAtomicRMWBinOp BinOp) {
3568  switch (BinOp) {
3569  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpXchg: return AtomicRMWInst::Xchg;
3570  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpAdd: return AtomicRMWInst::Add;
3571  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpSub: return AtomicRMWInst::Sub;
3572  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpAnd: return AtomicRMWInst::And;
3573  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpNand: return AtomicRMWInst::Nand;
3574  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpOr: return AtomicRMWInst::Or;
3575  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpXor: return AtomicRMWInst::Xor;
3576  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpMax: return AtomicRMWInst::Max;
3577  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpMin: return AtomicRMWInst::Min;
3578  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpUMax: return AtomicRMWInst::UMax;
3579  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpUMin: return AtomicRMWInst::UMin;
3580  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpFAdd: return AtomicRMWInst::FAdd;
3581  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpFSub: return AtomicRMWInst::FSub;
3582  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpFMax: return AtomicRMWInst::FMax;
3583  case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpFMin: return AtomicRMWInst::FMin;
3584  }
3585 
3586  llvm_unreachable("Invalid LLVMAtomicRMWBinOp value!");
3587 }
3588 
3589 static LLVMAtomicRMWBinOp mapToLLVMRMWBinOp(AtomicRMWInst::BinOp BinOp) {
3590  switch (BinOp) {
3591  case AtomicRMWInst::Xchg: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpXchg;
3592  case AtomicRMWInst::Add: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpAdd;
3593  case AtomicRMWInst::Sub: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpSub;
3594  case AtomicRMWInst::And: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpAnd;
3595  case AtomicRMWInst::Nand: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpNand;
3596  case AtomicRMWInst::Or: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpOr;
3597  case AtomicRMWInst::Xor: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpXor;
3598  case AtomicRMWInst::Max: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpMax;
3599  case AtomicRMWInst::Min: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpMin;
3600  case AtomicRMWInst::UMax: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpUMax;
3601  case AtomicRMWInst::UMin: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpUMin;
3602  case AtomicRMWInst::FAdd: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpFAdd;
3603  case AtomicRMWInst::FSub: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpFSub;
3604  case AtomicRMWInst::FMax: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpFMax;
3605  case AtomicRMWInst::FMin: return LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpFMin;
3606  default: break;
3607  }
3608 
3609  llvm_unreachable("Invalid AtomicRMWBinOp value!");
3610 }

3655 LLVMBool LLVMGetVolatile(LLVMValueRef MemAccessInst) {
3656  Value *P = unwrap(MemAccessInst);
3657  if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(P))
3658  return LI->isVolatile();
3659  if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(P))
3660  return SI->isVolatile();
3661  if (AtomicRMWInst *AI = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(P))
3662  return AI->isVolatile();
3663  return cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(P)->isVolatile();
3664 }
3665 
3666 void LLVMSetVolatile(LLVMValueRef MemAccessInst, LLVMBool isVolatile) {
3667  Value *P = unwrap(MemAccessInst);
3668  if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(P))
3669  return LI->setVolatile(isVolatile);
3670  if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(P))
3671  return SI->setVolatile(isVolatile);
3672  if (AtomicRMWInst *AI = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(P))
3673  return AI->setVolatile(isVolatile);
3674  return cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(P)->setVolatile(isVolatile);
3675 }

3684 
3685 LLVMAtomicOrdering LLVMGetOrdering(LLVMValueRef MemAccessInst) {
3686  Value *P = unwrap(MemAccessInst);
3687  AtomicOrdering O;
3688  if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(P))
3689  O = LI->getOrdering();
3690  else if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(P))
3691  O = SI->getOrdering();
3692  else
3693  O = cast<AtomicRMWInst>(P)->getOrdering();
3694  return mapToLLVMOrdering(O);
3695 }
3696 
3697 void LLVMSetOrdering(LLVMValueRef MemAccessInst, LLVMAtomicOrdering Ordering) {
3698  Value *P = unwrap(MemAccessInst);
3699  AtomicOrdering O = mapFromLLVMOrdering(Ordering);
3700 
3701  if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(P))
3702  return LI->setOrdering(O);
3703  return cast<StoreInst>(P)->setOrdering(O);
3704 }

3968 LLVMBool LLVMIsAtomicSingleThread(LLVMValueRef AtomicInst) {
3969  Value *P = unwrap(AtomicInst);
3970 
3971  if (AtomicRMWInst *I = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(P))
3972  return I->getSyncScopeID() == SyncScope::SingleThread;
3973  return cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(P)->getSyncScopeID() ==
3974  SyncScope::SingleThread;
3975 }

3977 void LLVMSetAtomicSingleThread(LLVMValueRef AtomicInst, LLVMBool NewValue) {
3978  Value *P = unwrap(AtomicInst);
3979  SyncScope::ID SSID = NewValue ? SyncScope::SingleThread : SyncScope::System;
3980 
3981  if (AtomicRMWInst *I = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(P))
3982  return I->setSyncScopeID(SSID);
3983  return cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(P)->setSyncScopeID(SSID);
3984 }

4026 LLVMBool LLVMCreateMemoryBufferWithContentsOfFile(
4027  const char *Path,
4028  LLVMMemoryBufferRef *OutMemBuf,
4029  char **OutMessage) {
4030 
4031  ErrorOr<std::unique_ptr<MemoryBuffer>> MBOrErr = MemoryBuffer::getFile(Path);
4032  if (std::error_code EC = MBOrErr.getError()) {
4033  *OutMessage = strdup(EC.message().c_str());
4034  return 1;
4035  }
4036  *OutMemBuf = wrap(MBOrErr.get().release());
4037  return 0;
4038 }

4043  if (std::error_code EC = MBOrErr.getError()) {
4044  *OutMessage = strdup(EC.message().c_str());
4045  return 1;
4046  }
4047  *OutMemBuf = wrap(MBOrErr.get().release());
4048  return 0;
